<section class="sec" style="padding-top:40px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="post-wrap post-body reveal">
<h2>Scroll-Stopping Videos for B2C Success on Social Media</h2> <p>Scroll-stopping videos help B2C brands dominate social media by delivering clear, engaging product messages in seconds — cutting through the noise where attention spans are shortest. They speed up the buying process, build credibility, and turn casual scrollers into customers.</p> <h2>The Modern Customer Journey Demands Clarity and Speed</h2> <p>Customers now research extensively online before ever talking to a sales team. A Gartner study found that 77% of B2B buyers say their last purchase was complicated or tough to navigate — showing just how crucial it is to simplify the buying process. <a href={p("services/how-to-video")}>Explainer videos</a> cut through that confusion, delivering product information in a way that's easy to understand, whether placed on your website or shared in emails and social feeds.</p> <h3>Visual Storytelling Simplifies Decision Making</h3> <p>Visual content helps people understand and remember more. Explainer videos combine visuals, storytelling, and sound to communicate effectively — Forrester research found that one minute of video is worth 1.8 million words. This ability to simplify and clarify is key to moving potential customers through the sales funnel.</p> <h2>Building Trust and Credibility with Clear Communication</h2> <p>Customers are far more likely to buy from brands that clearly explain how their products work and what benefits they offer. Animoto reports that 58% of consumers think companies with video content are more credible — a well-made video signals that your business is reliable and trustworthy.</p> <h2>Encouraging Action Through Strategic Calls to Action</h2> <p>The end of a video is just as important as the beginning. A clear, action-oriented CTA — booking a demo, downloading a resource, making a purchase — keeps the momentum going. Placing explainer videos on product pages can boost conversion rates by up to 80%.</p> <h2>Supporting Sales Teams with On-Demand Content</h2> <p>Explainer videos act like a sales team available 24/7, providing consistent messaging and answering prospect questions without a rep on standby. This is especially valuable in complex B2B sales, where teams use videos to reinforce discussions and help close deals more efficiently.</p> <h2>Optimizing the Buying Experience Across Channels</h2> <p>One of the best things about <a href={p("services/social-media-video")}>social media videos</a> is that they work across many channels — social platforms, email campaigns, and landing pages all extend their reach. Wyzowl reports that 86% of businesses use video as a marketing tool, and 84% say video has helped them generate leads.</p> <p>Similar principles apply to <a href={p("blog/the-competitive-advantage-product-video-production-gives")}>product videos that give brands a competitive edge</a> and to <a href={p("blog/how-viven-helps-brands-boost-customer-engagement-with-social-media-videos")}>boosting customer engagement with social media videos</a>.</p> <h2>Ready to Streamline Your Customer Buying Process?</h2> <p>At Viven, we specialize in creating scroll-stopping videos that make complex messages simple and speed up decision-making. <a href={p("contact")}>Let's make your business shine</a> with the power of video.</p>
    </div>
